<div class="code-container">
    <div class="code-header">
        <h1 class="code-title">Code of Conduct</h1>
        <p class="code-subtitle">
            Our community standards for safe, respectful, and inclusive participation
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="code-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Our Commitment</h2>
        <p class="section-content">
            Witch City Rope is committed to providing a safe, inclusive, and educational environment 
            for all members. This Code of Conduct outlines our community standards and expectations 
            for behavior at all events, gatherings, and interactions within our community.
        </p>
        <p class="section-content">
            By participating in our community, you agree to uphold these standards and contribute 
            to creating a positive experience for everyone involved.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="code-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Core Principles</h2>
        <div class="principles-list">
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Informed Consent:</strong> All activities require clear, enthusiastic, and ongoing consent from all participants. Consent can be withdrawn at any time.</li>
                <li><strong>Safety First:</strong> Physical and emotional safety are paramount. We maintain strict safety protocols and expect all members to prioritize risk awareness.</li>
                <li><strong>Respect for Boundaries:</strong> Everyone has the right to set and maintain their personal boundaries. These must be respected without question or pressure.</li>
                <li><strong>Inclusive Environment:</strong> We welcome people of all backgrounds, orientations, and experience levels. Discrimination is not tolerated.</li>
                <li><strong>Confidentiality:</strong> What happens in our community stays in our community. Respect others' privacy and personal information.</li>
                <li><strong>Educational Focus:</strong> We prioritize learning and skill development over performance or demonstration.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="code-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Expected Behavior</h2>
        <p class="section-content">
            All community members are expected to:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Treat all participants with respect and courtesy</li>
            <li>Communicate clearly and honestly about boundaries and interests</li>
            <li>Follow all safety protocols and guidelines</li>
            <li>Respect the decisions and comfort levels of others</li>
            <li>Maintain appropriate hygiene and dress standards</li>
            <li>Arrive on time and prepared for activities</li>
            <li>Contribute positively to the learning environment</li>
            <li>Support fellow community members in their journey</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="code-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Prohibited Behavior</h2>
        <p class="section-content">
            The following behaviors are strictly prohibited and may result in immediate removal and/or permanent ban:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Any form of harassment, intimidation, or discrimination</li>
            <li>Non-consensual touching or sexual contact</li>
            <li>Ignoring or pressuring someone to change their stated boundaries</li>
            <li>Attending events under the influence of drugs or alcohol</li>
            <li>Photography or recording without explicit consent</li>
            <li>Sharing personal information about other members</li>
            <li>Disrupting classes or events</li>
            <li>Unsafe practices that put others at risk</li>
            <li>Engaging in commercial activity without permission</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="violation-section">
        <h3 class="violation-title">Reporting Violations</h3>
        <p class="section-content">
            If you experience or witness behavior that violates this Code of Conduct, please report it immediately to:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Any event organizer or instructor present</li>
            <li>Our safety officer (identified at each event)</li>
            <li>Through our confidential reporting system</li>
            <li>Via email to safety@witchcityrope.com</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="section-content">
            All reports will be taken seriously and handled with discretion. We are committed to addressing 
            violations promptly and fairly.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="emergency-highlight">
        <div class="emergency-title">Emergency Situations</div>
        <p>If you are in immediate danger or experiencing a medical emergency, 
           call 911 first, then notify event organizers.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="code-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Consequences</h2>
        <p class="section-content">
            Violations of this Code of Conduct may result in:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Verbal warning and coaching</li>
            <li>Temporary suspension from events</li>
            <li>Mandatory safety refresher training</li>
            <li>Permanent ban from the community</li>
            <li>Notification to other communities (for serious violations)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="section-content">
            The severity of consequences will depend on the nature and severity of the violation, 
            as well as the member's history within our community.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="code-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Appeals Process</h2>
        <p class="section-content">
            If you believe you have been unfairly disciplined, you may appeal the decision by:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Submitting a written appeal within 30 days</li>
            <li>Providing any relevant evidence or witness statements</li>
            <li>Requesting a hearing with our leadership team</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="section-content">
            All appeals will be reviewed fairly and impartially by members of our leadership team 
            who were not involved in the original incident.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="code-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Updates and Changes</h2>
        <p class="section-content">
            This Code of Conduct may be updated periodically to reflect the evolving needs of our community. 
            All members will be notified of significant changes, and continued participation constitutes 
            acceptance of the updated terms.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="contact-section">
        <h2 class="contact-title">Questions or Concerns?</h2>
        <p class="contact-text">
            If you have questions about this Code of Conduct or need to report a violation, 
            please don't hesitate to reach out.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact" class="contact-button">Contact Us</a>
        <a href="mailto:safety@witchcityrope.com" class="contact-button">Report Concern</a>
    </div>
